TF-Agentic-Engine
Overview

This tool takes old or scanned infrastructure JSON files and turns them into clean Terraform code.

It uses a local AI model to generate the code, then checks the Terraform files for errors. If there are mistakes, it fixes them and tries again until the code is valid.

Core Architecture

The project is split into simple files:

main.py
Starts the program. It loads the mock infrastructure data and runs the engine.

src/agent.py
Builds the LangGraph workflow and creates the app.

src/nodes.py
Contains the main steps: Network, Security, Compute, Data, validation, and routing logic.

src/state.py
Stores the current state of the workflow and creates the first state.

src/utils.py
Contains helper functions, prompts, the LLM connection, code cleaning, file writing, and Terraform validation.

config/settings.py
Stores settings like the model name, Ollama URL, memory/context size, and max retry count.

Runtime Flow
Load data from scanner/mock_infra.json.
Create the starting state.
Generate Terraform code step by step:
Network
Security
Compute
Data
Save the generated code into terraform_workspace/.
Run terraform fmt to check the Terraform code.
If there are errors, go back to the correct step and fix them.
Repeat until the code is valid or the retry limit is reached.
Quick Start Guide
1. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
2. Check Ollama

Make sure Ollama is running, then download the model (or any other model):

ollama pull llama3.2
3. Update settings

Open:

config/settings.py

Update the model name and NUM_CTX value to match the model you are using.

4. Clean old Terraform files
rm -f terraform_workspace/*.tf
5. Run the project
python3 main.py
